[10:27] <masak> Vijay_: would it be possible to golf the example to just the distinction between <alpha> and <alnum>?

[10:28] <masak> (I'm really curious what charaters those are!)

[10:28] <masak> m: say so "a" ~~ /<alpha>/; say so "a" ~~ /<alnum>/

[10:28] <camelia> rakudo-moar b96f60ff7: OUTPUT: ¬´True‚ê§True‚ê§¬ª

[10:29] <masak> clearly "a" ain't it, for example ;)

[10:29] <Vijay_> My understanding is  <alpha> is [a-z_] and <alnum> is [0-9a-z_]

[10:30] <masak> m: say so "–±" ~~ /<alpha>/; say so "–±" ~~ /<alnum>/

[10:30] <camelia> rakudo-moar b96f60ff7: OUTPUT: ¬´True‚ê§True‚ê§¬ª

