[10:31] <masak> m: say so "Â≠ó" ~~ /<alpha>/; say so "Â≠ó" ~~ /<alnum>/

[10:31] <camelia> rakudo-moar b96f60ff7: OUTPUT: ¬´True‚ê§True‚ê§¬ª

[10:31] <masak> even a Chinese Â≠ó is alphabetic :)

[10:31] <masak> Vijay_: I'm still waiting for your alnum-but-not-alpha character

[10:32] <masak> m: say so "ƒ±" ~~ /<alpha>/; say so "ƒ±" ~~ /<alnum>/  # Turkish ƒ±

[10:32] <camelia> rakudo-moar b96f60ff7: OUTPUT: ¬´True‚ê§True‚ê§¬ª

[10:33] <masak> Vijay_: I think your main problem right now is that you have a big grammar and a hypothesis about what goes wrong in it, but no way to verify/falsify that hypothesis

[10:34] <masak> I'd advise making a copy of the grammar, and then gradually making the copy smaller, until it exposes *only* the thing you find surprising

[10:34] <masak> aka "golfing"

